25namespace {
26// The min probe packet size is scaled with the bitrate we're probing at.
27// This defines the max min probe packet size, meaning that on high bitrates
28// we have a min probe packet size of 200 bytes.
29constexpr DataSize kMinProbePacketSize = DataSize::Bytes(200);
30
31constexpr TimeDelta kProbeClusterTimeout = TimeDelta::Seconds(5);
32
33} // namespace
34
35BitrateProberConfig::BitrateProberConfig(
36 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config)
37 : min_probe_packets_sent("min_probe_packets_sent", 5),
38 min_probe_delta("min_probe_delta", TimeDelta::Millis(1)),
39 min_probe_duration("min_probe_duration", TimeDelta::Millis(15)),
40 max_probe_delay("max_probe_delay", TimeDelta::Millis(10)),
41 abort_delayed_probes("abort_delayed_probes", true) {
42 ParseFieldTrial(
43 {&min_probe_packets_sent, &min_probe_delta, &min_probe_duration,
44 &max_probe_delay, &abort_delayed_probes},
45 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-ProbingConfiguration"));
46 ParseFieldTrial(
47 {&min_probe_packets_sent, &min_probe_delta, &min_probe_duration,
48 &max_probe_delay, &abort_delayed_probes},
49 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-ProbingBehavior"));
50}
51
52BitrateProber::~BitrateProber() {
53 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_1000("WebRTC.BWE.Probing.TotalProbeClustersRequested",
54 total_probe_count_);
55 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_1000("WebRTC.BWE.Probing.TotalFailedProbeClusters",
56 total_failed_probe_count_);
57}
58
59BitrateProber::BitrateProber(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& field_trials)
60 : probing_state_(ProbingState::kDisabled),
61 next_probe_time_(Timestamp::PlusInfinity()),
62 total_probe_count_(0),
63 total_failed_probe_count_(0),
64 config_(&field_trials) {
65 SetEnabled(true);
66}
67
68void BitrateProber::SetEnabled(bool enable) {
69 if (enable) {
70 if (probing_state_ == ProbingState::kDisabled) {
71 probing_state_ = ProbingState::kInactive;
72 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Bandwidth probing enabled, set to inactive";
73 }
74 } else {
75 probing_state_ = ProbingState::kDisabled;
76 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Bandwidth probing disabled";
77 }
78}
79
80void BitrateProber::OnIncomingPacket(DataSize packet_size) {
81 // Don't initialize probing unless we have something large enough to start
82 // probing.
83 if (probing_state_ == ProbingState::kInactive && !clusters_.empty() &&
84 packet_size >= std::min(RecommendedMinProbeSize(), kMinProbePacketSize)) {
85 // Send next probe right away.
86 next_probe_time_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
87 probing_state_ = ProbingState::kActive;
88 }
89}
90
91void BitrateProber::CreateProbeCluster(DataRate bitrate,
92 Timestamp now,
93 int cluster_id) {
94 RTC_DCHECK(probing_state_ != ProbingState::kDisabled);
95 RTC_DCHECK_GT(bitrate, DataRate::Zero());
96
97 total_probe_count_++;
98 while (!clusters_.empty() &&
99 now - clusters_.front().created_at > kProbeClusterTimeout) {
100 clusters_.pop();
101 total_failed_probe_count_++;
102 }
103
104 ProbeCluster cluster;
105 cluster.created_at = now;
106 cluster.pace_info.probe_cluster_min_probes = config_.min_probe_packets_sent;
107 cluster.pace_info.probe_cluster_min_bytes =
108 (bitrate * config_.min_probe_duration.Get()).bytes();
109 RTC_DCHECK_GE(cluster.pace_info.probe_cluster_min_bytes, 0);
110 cluster.pace_info.send_bitrate_bps = bitrate.bps();
111 cluster.pace_info.probe_cluster_id = cluster_id;
112 clusters_.push(cluster);
113
114 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Probe cluster (bitrate:min bytes:min packets): ("
115 << cluster.pace_info.send_bitrate_bps << ":"
116 << cluster.pace_info.probe_cluster_min_bytes << ":"
117 << cluster.pace_info.probe_cluster_min_probes << ")";
118 // If we are already probing, continue to do so. Otherwise set it to
119 // kInactive and wait for OnIncomingPacket to start the probing.
120 if (probing_state_ != ProbingState::kActive)
121 probing_state_ = ProbingState::kInactive;
122}
123
124Timestamp BitrateProber::NextProbeTime(Timestamp now) const {
125 // Probing is not active or probing is already complete.
126 if (probing_state_ != ProbingState::kActive || clusters_.empty()) {
127 return Timestamp::PlusInfinity();
128 }
129
130 // Legacy behavior, just warn about late probe and return as if not probing.
131 if (!config_.abort_delayed_probes && next_probe_time_.IsFinite() &&
132 now - next_probe_time_ > config_.max_probe_delay.Get()) {
133 RTC_DLOG(LS_WARNING) << "Probe delay too high"
134 " (next_ms:"
135 << next_probe_time_.ms() << ", now_ms: " << now.ms()
136 << ")";
137 return Timestamp::PlusInfinity();
138 }
139
140 return next_probe_time_;
141}
142
143absl::optional<PacedPacketInfo> BitrateProber::CurrentCluster(Timestamp now) {
144 if (clusters_.empty() || probing_state_ != ProbingState::kActive) {
145 return absl::nullopt;
146 }
147
148 if (config_.abort_delayed_probes && next_probe_time_.IsFinite() &&
149 now - next_probe_time_ > config_.max_probe_delay.Get()) {
150 RTC_DLOG(LS_WARNING) << "Probe delay too high"
151 " (next_ms:"
152 << next_probe_time_.ms() << ", now_ms: " << now.ms()
153 << "), discarding probe cluster.";
154 clusters_.pop();
155 if (clusters_.empty()) {
156 probing_state_ = ProbingState::kSuspended;
157 return absl::nullopt;
158 }
159 }
160
161 PacedPacketInfo info = clusters_.front().pace_info;
162 info.probe_cluster_bytes_sent = clusters_.front().sent_bytes;
163 return info;
164}
165
166// Probe size is recommended based on the probe bitrate required. We choose
167// a minimum of twice |kMinProbeDeltaMs| interval to allow scheduling to be
168// feasible.
169DataSize BitrateProber::RecommendedMinProbeSize() const {
170 if (clusters_.empty()) {
171 return DataSize::Zero();
172 }
173 DataRate send_rate =
174 DataRate::BitsPerSec(clusters_.front().pace_info.send_bitrate_bps);
175 return 2 * send_rate * config_.min_probe_delta;
176}
177
178void BitrateProber::ProbeSent(Timestamp now, DataSize size) {
179 RTC_DCHECK(probing_state_ == ProbingState::kActive);
180 RTC_DCHECK(!size.IsZero());
181
182 if (!clusters_.empty()) {
183 ProbeCluster* cluster = &clusters_.front();
184 if (cluster->sent_probes == 0) {
185 RTC_DCHECK(cluster->started_at.IsInfinite());
186 cluster->started_at = now;
187 }
188 cluster->sent_bytes += size.bytes<int>();
189 cluster->sent_probes += 1;
190 next_probe_time_ = CalculateNextProbeTime(*cluster);
191 if (cluster->sent_bytes >= cluster->pace_info.probe_cluster_min_bytes &&
192 cluster->sent_probes >= cluster->pace_info.probe_cluster_min_probes) {
193 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.BWE.Probing.ProbeClusterSizeInBytes",
194 cluster->sent_bytes);
195 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100("WebRTC.BWE.Probing.ProbesPerCluster",
196 cluster->sent_probes);
197 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_10000("WebRTC.BWE.Probing.TimePerProbeCluster",
198 (now - cluster->started_at).ms());
199
200 clusters_.pop();
201 }
202 if (clusters_.empty()) {
203 probing_state_ = ProbingState::kSuspended;
204 }
205 }
206}
207
208Timestamp BitrateProber::CalculateNextProbeTime(
209 const ProbeCluster& cluster) const {
210 RTC_CHECK_GT(cluster.pace_info.send_bitrate_bps, 0);
211 RTC_CHECK(cluster.started_at.IsFinite());
212
213 // Compute the time delta from the cluster start to ensure probe bitrate stays
214 // close to the target bitrate. Result is in milliseconds.
215 DataSize sent_bytes = DataSize::Bytes(cluster.sent_bytes);
216 DataRate send_bitrate =
217 DataRate::BitsPerSec(cluster.pace_info.send_bitrate_bps);
218 TimeDelta delta = sent_bytes / send_bitrate;
219 return cluster.started_at + delta;
220}
